Great French cuisine in a semi-formal setting. Went on Christmas Eve, was slightly disappointed they did not offer a special menu. But later, realized they don't need as their regular menu served the purpose. The escargot and wine was excellent. The orange duck was okay, meat a bit dry. Would come again to try their special French chicken and T-bone!

Let's start with the good - the chef is excellent.  Unfortunately totally let down by front of house. At this price point I would expect attentive thoughtful service. There was none, we had to continually seek a waiter for glasses, cutlery, bread (one of our table was just not offered bread). Such a shame.

Wo woo wooo, such a fine dining place. Nice place enjoy the music, place, people and food. The most favorite UK restaurant open in down town Central. Every bugs you spent is worth it. Why don’t you make yourself nice. Go enjoy it.
Top spot in Hong Kong. Not suitable for a quiet conversation.

result.name: Vive Cake Boutique (Central)

reviews.text: It is a very fancy little cafe with some really attractive cakes and amazing intricate designs. They were expensive but did taste really good. If you fancy a short break and want to treat yourself and maybe for the gram pic, this place is worth a try. I enjoyed it!!

Looking for some sweet little treats in this Summer?  Look no further, here are some adorable mini cakes for every sweet tooth.

Flamingo Floatie (HK$55)
This lovely bubblegum pink ‘Flamingo Floatie’ is sure to please everyone, made with vanilla sponge, jasmine jelly, and oolong chocolate mousse, which makes it even more delightful.

Limesicle (HK$55)
This popsicle-like cake is full of fresh summer flavours, with vanilla sponge cake, lime jelly filling and coated with yogurt mousse.   The refreshing lime jelly filling gives the cake an extra punch of flavour and it’s perfect for these long hot days of summer.

Mini-Cone (HK$58)
Who dropped the ice cream on the plate?  No worries! That’s a mini version of VIVE’s signature uni-cone cake.  Featuring an upside down “ice-cream” cone looks  like a dropped ice cream.  I really like how it was not overly sweet!

Watermelon Mojito (HK$68)
This watermelon mojito is utterly stunning and irresistible refreshing.

Grapefruit and Lime Soda (HK$65)
The grapefruit and lime soda is the best low-calorie thirst quencher, simple yet refreshing!
Lovely Barbie cakes 🥴

《閨蜜聚蛋糕之選》
早前聖誕節期間，遇上一個讓所有在場女生都心心眼的蛋糕，説的是Vive Cake Boutique出品的 Let It Snow 節日限定版Carrot cake甘筍蛋糕。

Let It Snow 蛋糕一如Vive Cake Boutique出品的一貫精緻風格，蛋糕色彩繽紛，而且上面還有一隻小鹿，十分可愛。蛋糕彩色外層的是忌廉滑溜，甘筍蛋糕質感稍微偏乾身，但勝在甜度適中。吃完一大塊蛋糕也不會有太大罪惡感，加上賣相超美，絕對是閨蜜聚會蛋糕之選呢～
很漂亮的甜點店，甜品飲料也很夢幻

reviews.text: With excellent art throughout the year , the galleries here are always chopping and changing something new every few months. A real eclectic mix of artists; some well known, others less so, there's also piqnic on the roof for a well earned bevy.

The art was great but the accessibility of the building is horrible. I injured my knee and ankle earlier in the day and despite having a visible limp, the guards had to be asked repeatedly for the lift and only begrudgingly called for the elevator when I was going 3 and 5 floors down. For single floors I just hobbled down because they made such a big production out of it when I was going multiple floors.
Nice building. The janitors downstairs, they are a little pushy because of the crowd they get.
Very very great place to visit. And of cuz to see art and buy art.
House the majority of the quality art galleries  of Hong Kong
